Hi NFV Friends,
<br><br>
Welcome to our newest members - <strong>Ixia</strong> and <strong>AudioCodes</strong>!
<br><br>
The ecosystem program is growing and new members are joining us to work 
on CloudBand, the Platform for NFV. This month I would like to highlight
 some interesting things we are working on with Intel and Redhat.
<br><br>
Intel and ALU are working together to expose performance enhancers such 
as DPDK and NUMA thought the CloudBand Management System that will allow
 workloads to be deployed on VMs while meeting specific performance 
requirements such as jitter, low latency -- very powerful for data plane
 applications!
<br><br>
Red Hat and ALU are building over OpenStack the specific NFV 
requirements that Telcos need: a higher level of orchestration, 
application lifecycle management, the capacity to manage workloads 
across distributed data centers, SLA management, and specific security 
features for operations.
<br><br>
We believe this work with two major technology players will benefit our entire ecosystem community. 
<br><br>
Hope to see you soon,<br>
Valerie Noto<br>
Director CloudBand Ecosystem Program

